# endSheet(_:returnCode:)

**Instance Method**

Ends a document modal session by specifying the sheet window.

## Declaration

```swift
@MainActor func endSheet(_ sheet: NSWindow, returnCode: Int)
```

## Parameters

- **sheet**: The sheet whose modal session you want to end.
- **returnCode**: The return code to send to the delegate. You can use one of the return codes defined in [doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSApplication/ModalResponse] or a custom value that you define.

## Methods

- **activate(ignoringOtherApps:)**: Makes the receiver the active app.
- **endModalSession(_:)**: Finishes a modal session.
- **beginSheet(_:modalFor:modalDelegate:didEnd:contextInfo:)**: Starts a document modal session.
- **endSheet(_:)**: Ends a document modal session by specifying the sheet window.
